title: Bug 114470[Smoke] Error message throws when using new Date('3/2/2005') as value in table filter.
OB: When using the value 'new Date('3/2/2005')' in a table filter, an error message is thrown.
EB: The system should accept and properly handle the value 'new Date('3/2/2005')' as a valid input in the table filter without throwing an error.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Open the table filter.
2. Set the filter value to 'new Date('3/2/2005')'.
3. Apply the filter.
